trend_summary: Across the sequence, the peninsula stays predominantly agricultural. Built-up footprints expand only slightly around the central village/industrial node and along a few roads. Field patterns shift with crop rotation, while several plots revert to woodland or pasture. Infrastructure improvements are minor, so the overall character remains sparsely developed and rural.
notable_changes: Modest outward growth and infill of the central settlement/industrial complex.
New scattered farmsteads and auxiliary sheds appear beside main roads.
Several large fields switch from bare soil to vegetated cover, indicating crop rotation.
Incremental expansion of woodland patches, especially in the eastern tongue.
Minor road upgrades and a new straight access track leading to the central complex.
